-- Gerry Weber buys Hallhuber from Change Capital Partners
-- By Maria Sheahan
-- Mon Dec 22, 2014 11:34AM EST
-- None



FRANKFURT, Dec 22 (Reuters) - Germany's Gerry Weber <GWIG.DE> said on Monday it had agreed to buy fashion group Hallhuber from private equity firm Change Capital Partners LLP, expanding into a market catering to women in their mid-twenties and above.

Hallhuber will start making a positive contribution to Gerry Weber's operating profit and earnings per share in the financial year through the end of October 2015, Gerry Weber said in a statement.